wp is mobile "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
============================================================

NAME
----

wp is mobile - This Conditional Tag checks if the user is visiting using a mobile

SYNOPSIS
--------

This Conditional Tag checks if the user is visiting using a mobile
device. This is a boolean function, meaning it returns either TRUE or
FALSE.

USAGE
-----

` <?php wp_is_mobile(); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

EXAMPLES
--------

    <?php if ( wp_is_mobile() ) {
        /* Display and echo mobile specific stuff here */
    } ?>

CHANGE LOG
----------

-   Since: 3.4

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`wp_is_mobile()` is located in `wp-includes/vars.php`.

See also index of [Function
Reference](/Function_Reference "Function Reference") and index of
[Template Tags](/Template_Tags "Template Tags").

